{
  "_comment": "Context window limits for models accessible via Pi terminal harness (pi.dev). Values are total context in tokens. Organized by Pi built-in provider name. Update periodically -- run /model in Pi to see current available models.",
  "_updated": "2026-05-06",
  "_source": "https://pi.dev/models, provider docs, OpenRouter",

  "defaults": {
    "conservative": 128000,
    "minimum_safe": 32000
  },

  "detection": {
    "how_to_determine_your_limit": [
      "1. In Pi, check bottom-right of TUI for active model name.",
      "2. Run: node -e \"const d=require('./model-context-limits.json'); const m=process.argv[1]; const v=Object.values(d.providers).flatMap(p=>Object.entries(p)).find(([k])=>m.includes(k)); console.log(v?v[1]:d.defaults.conservative)\" YOUR_MODEL",
      "3. If no match, use defaults.conservative (128000).",
      "4. Regardless of limit, always prefer context-mode sandbox for large outputs."
    ]
  },

